{"lemma":"شَرْقِيّ","slug":"شَرْقِيّ","root":"ش.ر.ق","root_slug":"ش-ر-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَرْقِيّ","root":"شرق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22200"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"eastern","examples":[{"text":"Coordinate term: غَرْبِيّ (ḡarbiyy)"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Eastern, Oriental"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"شَرْق (šarq, “east”) + ـِيّ (-iyy), from the root ش ر ق (š r q)."},"ipa":["/ʃar.qijj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22200","headword_ar":"شَرْقِىٌّ","root":"$rq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating to, the east,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of sunrise; eastern,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oriental"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA $aroqiy~api walaA garobiy~apK","text_ar":"لَا شَرْقِيَّةِ وَلَا غَرْبِيَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) in the Kur [xxiv. 35], (TA,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Not such that the sun shines upon it at its rising only"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor at its setting only,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but such that the sun lights upon it morning and evening:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K, TA:) or, accord. to El- Hasan, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not of the trees of the people of the present world, but of the trees of the people of Paradise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Az, however, says that the former explanation is more fit and more commonly receive. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnN $aroqiY~N","text_ar":"مَكَانٌ شَرْقِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place, of the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground, in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, which the sun rises,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shines."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAriqN","text_ar":"شَارِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariqN","text_ar":"شَرِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oruqapN","text_ar":"مَشْرُقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"].       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain red dye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Fr"]}]}}